### E2E simulation: Event Grid -> Service Bus -> DB
#
# Shortcut: spring.profiles.active=local,e2e
# Closer to Azure (Grid only; SB via Portal subscription): spring.profiles.active=local,e2e-azure
#
# Env: AZURE_EVENTGRID_TOPIC_ENDPOINT, AZURE_EVENTGRID_TOPIC_KEY,
#      AZURE_SERVICEBUS_CONNECTION_STRING, AZURE_SERVICEBUS_ENTITY=<queue>
# Portal (e2e-azure): Event Subscription on topic -> same queue as ENTITY.
# After app is UP: add a NEW xml under storage/2026-04-18/ (see ORD-*.sample.xml)
# GET /api/ingest/storage-events

### Study notes (no Azure)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/review

### OpenAPI JSON
GET http://localhost:8080/api-docs

### Swagger UI
# http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html

### Storage info (date folders, watch root)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/storage/info

### Create virtual order XML (saved under today's date folder)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/storage/virtual-orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 199.5,
  "userName": "Jane Doe",
  "phone": "+1-555-0100",
  "paymentMethod": "CreditCard"
}


### Last ingested rows (PostgreSQL, after Service Bus consumer persists)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/ingest/storage-events

### Event Grid sample publish (requires demo.azure.event-grid.enabled=true and topic config)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/event-grid/publish-sample

#
# Maven with debug port 5005, then attach "Attach: Remote (5005)":
#   mvn spring-boot:run -Pdebug
#
